Everest Re Group, Ltd. (RE) Holdings Up in Latest Report from Aperio Group, LLC - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Everest Re Group, Ltd. (RE) Holdings Up in Latest Report from Aperio Group, LLC
July 19, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Everest Re Group, Ltd. (NYSE:RE). 
 Aperio Group, LLC reports that it raised its investment in Everest Re Group, Ltd. shares by 16,557 shares in a 13F filing with the SEC.  Its stake stood at $80,095,000 an increase of 14.9% as of the end of the quarter. 
 Aperio Group, LLC isn’t the only one who has changed their investment in RE.   Ls Investment Advisors, LLC downsized its ownership by selling 1,834 shares a decrease of 3.5% as of 06/30/2017. Ls Investment Advisors, LLC owns 50,308 shares valued at $12,808,000. The total value of its holdings increased 5.1%. As of quarter end Nisa Investment Advisors, LLC had disposed of  a total of 3,741 shares trimming its holdings by 12.7%. The value of the investment in Everest Re Group, Ltd. decreased from $6,874,000 to $6,533,000 a change of $341,000 for the reporting period.
 As of the end of the quarter Oregon Public Employees Retirement Fund had sold 12,216 shares trimming its stake by 48.1%. The value of the investment in RE went from $5,943,000 to $3,361,000 decreasing 43.4% since the last quarter.
  On July 17 the company was downgraded from “Market Perform” to “Underperform” by analysts at Keefe Bruyette & Woods. On November 15 the stock rating was upgraded to “Neutral” from “” in an announcement from Goldman Sachs.





 July 27 investment analysts at Keefe Bruyette & Woods held the company rating at “Market Perform” but moved up the price target from $185.00 to $204.00. On May 12 Deutsche Bank made no change to the stock rating of “Buy” and moved up the price target  to $209.00 from $205.00.
 February 8 investment analysts at Keefe Bruyette & Woods held the stock rating at “Market Perform” but raised the price target from $192.00 to $200.00. Equity analyst Sterne Agee CRT starting coverage on the stock by announcing an initial rating of “Neutral”.
 The company is so far trading up from yesterday’s close of $264.86.  Everest Re Group, Ltd. also announced a dividend for shareholders paid on Wednesday the 14th of June 2017.  The dividend was $1.250 per share for the quarter which comes to $5.00 on an annualized basis.  The dividend yield was $1.90.  The ex-dividend date was set for Friday the 26th of May 2017. 
 Shares of the company are trading at $267.33 a tad higher than the 50 day moving average of $257.38 and which is just a bit higher than the 200 day moving average of $239.78.  The 50 day moving average moved up $9.95 and the 200 day average was up $27.55. 
 Everest Re Group, Ltd.’s P/E ratio is 9.98 and the market cap of the company is 10.98B.  In the latest earnings report the EPS was $26.80 and is estimated to be $20.92 for the current year with 41,069,000 shares presently outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS will be $3.73 with next year’s EPS anticipated to be $20.61. 






