Everest Re Group, Ltd. Key Developments

Everest Re Group, Ltd. Appoints Matthew Kelly to Head its International Casualty Facultative Operation
Jun 22 17
Everest Re Group, Ltd. announced that Matthew Kelly has joined the Group as Vice President and Head of the Reinsurance Division’s International Casualty Facultative unit and is based in Everest Re’s Miami Office. He will be responsible for worldwide Casualty facultative underwriting, excluding business written for U.S. and Canada clients. Matt joins Everest with more than 20 years of industry experience, most recently as Regional Head of Casualty and Specialty Casualty with Hiscox. Matt had previously headed up the Casualty and Specialty Casualty underwriting practice for prominent carriers in Latin America and Caribbean. His experience includes insurance operations overseas in Mexico, Puerto Rico, and Argentina.


Everest Re Group, Ltd. Declares Dividend, Payable on or Before June 14, 2017
May 17 17
Everest Re Group, Ltd. announced that its Board of Directors declared a dividend of $1.25 per share payable on or before June 14, 2017 to all shareholders of record as of May 31, 2017.


Everest Re Group Ltd. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
Apr 24 17
Everest Re Group Ltd. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported total revenues of $1,484,778,000 against $1,242,046,000 last year. Premiums earned were $1,312,097,000 against $1,218,867,000 a year ago. Net investment income was $122,289,000 against $102,524,000 a year ago. Income before taxes was $338,413,000 against $177,067,000 a year ago. Net income was $291,643,000 against $171,686,000 a year ago. Diluted earnings per share were $7.07 against $4.00 a year ago. Net cash provided by operating activities was $381,812,000 against $375,476,000 a year ago. The annualized after-tax operating income return on average adjusted shareholders’ equity was 12.8%. Book value per share increased 3% from $197.45 at December 31, 2016 to $203.32 at March 31, 2017. After-tax operating income was $259,533,000 or $6.29 per diluted share against $222,665,000 or $5.19 per diluted share a year ago.


